entries.title: A Crypto Magnate Saw the Risks and Still Was Hammered
entries.description: CEO Barry Silbert of Digital Currency Group, a finance veteran who built a crypto conglomerate, now is fighting to keep its lending firm out of bankruptcy.

entries.title: Apple Rolls Out Latest MacBook Pro With New M2 Chips
entries.description: The enhancements enable a more power-efficient performance and battery life, with prices of new MacBook models ranging from $1,999 to $2,499.

entries.title: Google Didn't Show Bias in Filtering Campaign-Ad Pitches, FEC Says
entries.description: GOP committees had cited an academic article to claim Google’s spam filters were designed to benefit Democrats.

entries.title: U.K. to Toughen New Social-Media Law, Threatening CEOs With Jail Time
entries.description: The Online Safety Bill aims to better protect adults and children from viewing certain online content, including fraud, revenge porn and sexual abuse.

entries.title: Activision Says NetEase Rejected Offer to Extend China Licensing Partnership
entries.description: Activision Blizzard said it is in talks with several videogame firms to find a new partner in China.

entries.title: EU Readies Subsidy Response to U.S. Clean-Tech Tax Breaks
entries.description: Europe aims to provide more support to its domestic clean-tech industry in a push to counter subsidies from the U.S. and China, European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen said.

entries.title: The Latest TikTok Star Is Canned Tuna
entries.description: Riding a wave of online popularity among young foodies, canned-fish sellers are launching new products, expanding production and working with social-media influencers.

entries.title: Microsoft Plans to Build OpenAI Capabilities Into All Products
entries.description: The software giant plans to incorporate artificial-intelligence tools from the startup and make them available as platforms for other businesses to build on, CEO Satya Nadella said at a WSJ-hosted panel in Davos.

entries.title: Microsoft Expands Access to OpenAI's Tools
entries.description: ChatGPT, which has recently gained attention for its ability to write essays, is among the startup’s AI products.
